Description: TuneUp Media is a platform creating a better digital music experience for music lovers.
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: TuneUp Media was created for music lovers, by music lovers, with the sole purpose of creating a better digital music experience for everyone. It's flagship product, TuneUp has quickly become the #1 selling plug-in for iTunes that also supports Windows Media Player, and has amassed millions of registered users worldwide. Founded in 2007 by avid music lover and industry leader, Gabriel Adiv, TuneUp was born out of personal frustration with the shortcomings of his own digital music library. He had too many songs titled "Track 01", no cover art, and no easy means of accessing additional album, artist or concert information. Everything he loved about his vinyl and CD collection was lost in translation, as the digital music industry scrambled to catch up. TuneUp Media develops products to not only address these issues, but also tap the broader digital and social media universe to create an experience far beyond anything Gabe could have found in his liner notes. Now, millions of digital music consumers around the world have used TuneUp to clean up and organize their music metadata, intelligently find and remove duplicate songs, fill in missing album cover art, explore their world of music and share it with friends. Best of all, TuneUp works "automagically". Behind it's simple interface lies cutting-edge acoustic fingerprinting technology, backed by the Gracenote's MusicID, the world's largest database of music-related metadata, boasting over 90 million indexed tracks.
Industry Groups: Internet Services, Media and Entertainment, Music and Audio, Software

Description: Proxomo Software offers a cloud and BaaS-based platform that enables developers to build and deploy mobile apps.
Full Description: Proxomo resides at the intersection of mobile app development and cloud-based, server-side mobile services to make app development quicker and easier to deploy for individual developers, enterprise developers and agency partners.  Our solutions leverage cross platform development to deliver robust mobile solutions and backend as a service (BaaS) cloud technology that enables web and mobile innovators to build and deploy feature rich, highly scalable, ultra secure apps much faster.   Proxomo enables app developers to store, manage and access their data via the cloud and develop backend features for apps in the shortest time possible.  Proxomo was named one of Gartner Group’s six “Cool Vendors in Context-Aware Computing” for 2011 and is based in Dallas, Texas.  For more information, visit http://www.proxomo.com Proxomo’s unique offerings include:  The Proxomo BaaS Platform is a RESTful API that cross integrates a variety of context services designed to simplify the development of context-aware applications, including location, collaboration (both e-mail and SMS) and social networking. Proxomo functions as an abstraction layer, shielding developers from the complexity involved in directly integrating a variety of context agents, while simultaneously enriching the services it provides with additional functionality (such as application data storage, centralized user profile authentication and management, and user events). The JUMPSTART Developer Platform helps software developers minimize repetitive tasks while providing unlimited flexibility for a developer to extend the abilities of their code without any limitation being set by the development platform or libraries. Benefits of the Proxomo offering suite: •	Speeds development and deployment of mobile and web apps. •	Easier for developers to setup, use and operate a cloud backend for their mobile, tablet and web apps. •	Simplifies the development of context-aware applications (location, collaboration, social networking). •	Reduces operational costs and processes Specialties Mobile, Mobile applications, iOS, Android, Backend Development, Push Notifications, Social Integration, API Creation

Full Description: Curonz is a clinical stage biotechnology company with a drug portfolio covering the peptide family, Neural Regeneration Peptides (NRPs), which were discovered by Curonz's founding Director, Dr Frank Sieg and where precursor compounds to our clinical molecule NRP2945 were first patented back in 2001. NRP2945 exerts its activity via agonism of a novel CXCR4 receptor complex in an ultra-potent manner with no off-target effects. Description: Folding@home is a distributed computing project for disease research that simulates protein folding, computational drug design, and other
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: Folding@home is a distributed computing project for disease research that simulates protein folding, computational drug design, and other types of molecular dynamics. The project uses the idle processing resources of thousands of personal computers owned by volunteers who have installed the software on their systems. Its primary purpose is to determine the mechanisms of protein folding, which is the process by which proteins reach their final three-dimensional structure, and to examine the causes of protein misfolding. It is developed and operated by the Pande Laboratory at Stanford University, under the direction of Professor Vijay Pande, and is shared by various scientific institutions and research laboratories across the world. Folding@home is one of the world's fastest computing systems, with a speed of approximately 18 petaFLOPS. Since its launch on October 1, 2000, the Pande lab has produced 109 scientific research papers as a direct result of Folding@home.

Full Description: [Tools.Valarm.net](http://Tools.Valarm.net) Software Saves Your Organization's Time + Money by Monitoring Water, Air, Tanks, Levels, & Any Assets with Industrial IoT Sensors. Learn more about who uses Valarm's Industrial IoT applications on [our customer stories page](http://www.valarm.net/customer-stories/). Valarm brings Industrial IoT to your business intelligence / analytics systems like the Esri ArcGIS platform. [Valarm Tools Cloud](http://tools.valarm.net) gives you real-time access to your Industrial IoT information monitoring any of your assets like: - [Flood Warning Systems monitoring water levels, coastal areas, rising tides, storm surges, natural disasters and emergency response for Your Smart Cities](http://www.valarm.net/flood-warning-systems/) - [Water & fluids monitoring](http://www.valarm.net/markets/water-monitoring-solutions-and-systems/) - [Remotely Monitoring Fire Risk + Meteorology Sensors in Southern California](http://www.valarm.net/blog/web-dashboards-for-remotely-monitoring-fire-risk-meteorology-sensors-in-southern-california/) - [Water Well Telemetry: Levels + Flowmeters](http://www.valarm.net/blog/remote-water-well-telemetry-with-a-web-dashboard-to-see-levels-and-flow-meter-rates/) - [Real-Time Remote Tank Sensor Monitoring](http://www.valarm.net/blog/web-dashboards-for-real-time-remote-tank-sensor-monitoring/) - [Monitoring water levels for effective water management in the oil & gas / petroleum / natural resources industries](http://www.valarm.net/blog/water-level-monitoring-for-the-upstream-oil-gas-industry/) - [Pollution and Air Quality Monitoring Systems working with environmental consultancies and AQMD, the California government agency responsible for air quality compliance and monitoring](http://www.valarm.net/blog/adventures-in-air-quality-monitoring-with-industrial-iot-sensors-and-california-government/)
